text: From the twitter archives, a post by Gait on "long pig"

Bobby Fischer accused many of his opponents of being "chess geniuses", machine-like overspecialized eunuchs who were unable to function outside the sphere of chess.

At the end of his career he was only player who "didn't trust computers and wasn't surrounded by consultants".

The way to see if a man has real "genius" is if it not limited to one subject, but instead spreads into all other areas of knowledge. If a writer has no opinions about art, or a painter lacks theological and mathematical theories - he is likely more or less a hack.
Loss of appetite is an omen of death and disease.

If you have skipped your leg workout and have decided to overhead press, you might as well try Thrusters instead. 

A very good full-body exercise that almost no one ever does.
